[{"content":"\u003ch2 id=\"background\"\u003eBackground\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCSC-405 was a class at North Carolina State University (NCSU) built on learning about offensive security. The major topics covered were Low-Level Code Vulnerabilities, Shellcodes, Reverse Engineering, Linux Security, Web Security, and LLM Security.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe class focused on practical application first, where content was mainly taught by showcasing the technical steps \u0026amp;  reasoning leading up to a vulnerability. For example, to learn how to perform Shellcode attacks, we, in order:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLearned the necessary steps to create x86 Assembly language programs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLearned to extract the binary values of a program \u0026amp; how to verify the program hasn\u0026rsquo;t been tampered with.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLearned to convert only the program\u0026rsquo;s executable bytes into a Hex form like \u003ccode\u003e\\x48\\xc7\\...\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLearned to create a custom assembly program to spawn a shell in the current context.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLearned how to combine the above to inject a shell into a controlled remote server for execution\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe assignment structure of the course was also unlike any other I had taken. The course was comprised of 4 assignments, each akin to Capture the Flag (CTF) challenges comprised of multiple levels each. It starts off simple and easy to introduce the base concept, but then quickly ramps up in difficulty as you progress. From start to end, 1 hour solves can evolve into 3-5 day solves. The first 3 were hosted directly by the teaching staff and were very fundamental in teaching offensive security concepts to me. The final assignment was to partake in Hackpack\u0026rsquo;s 2024 CTF, which was\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"work-performed\"\u003eWork Performed\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am not allowed to post the specifics of the work I performed on each challenge due to content being coursework materials, but I can describe what I performed for each challenge.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch3 id=\"challenge-1-shellcodes\"\u003eChallenge 1: Shellcodes\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"highlight\"\u003e\u003cpre tabindex=\"0\" style=\"color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;\"\u003e\u003ccode class=\"language-html\" data-lang=\"html\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#75715e\"\u003e\u0026lt;!DOCTYPE html\u0026gt;\u003c/span\u003e\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026lt;\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003ehtml\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan style=\"color:#a6e22e\"\u003elang\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#e6db74\"\u003e\u0026#34;en\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e  \u0026lt;\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003ehead\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e    \u0026lt;\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003emeta\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan style=\"color:#a6e22e\"\u003echarset\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003e=\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#e6db74\"\u003e\u0026#34;UTF-8\u0026#34;\u003c/span\u003e /\u0026gt;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e    \u0026lt;\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003etitle\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;Example HTML5 Document\u0026lt;/\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003etitle\u003c/span\u003e\u0026gt;\n\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan style=\"display:flex;\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e  \u0026lt;/\u003cspan style=\"color:#f92672\"\u003